EVA FLORENCE HUBER v. BALTIMORE TRUST COMPANY, Executor and Trustee. [No. 22,

October Term, 1929.]

Decided October 31st, 1929.

The cause was argued before Bond, 0. J., Pattison, Urner, Adkins, Oeeutt, Digges, Parke, and Sloan, JJ.

W. LeBoy Oriel, for the appellant. Semmes, Bowen & Bemmes, submitting on motion to dismiss, for the appellee.

A per curiam opinion was delivered.
